{"article_id":"QO3Inz5sXEyivlnx","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The printing presses are rolling on the 2020 census ,","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"but the Justice Department says","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"it has been instructed to find a new way","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"to ask responders a controversial question about citizenship .","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"The 2020 census form has gone to the presses .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"The form does not have a question","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"asking people","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"whether they are U.S. citizens .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"The Trump administration wanted that question on the form ,","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"but the Supreme Court said","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"no for now .","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"But then yesterday , an official at the Justice Department said","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"they have been told to keep looking for a way","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"to ask this question anyway .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"It appears this was prompted in part by a tweet from President Trump","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"suggesting","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"that he has not really given up on this .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"Hansi Lo Wang has been covering the census extensively .","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"Hi , Hansi .","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"KING :","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"OK .","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"So this is a developing story","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"that just keeps developing in surprising ways .","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"Can you explain","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"what 's happening now with the Department of Justice ?","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"WANG :","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"This is all over this question","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"that asks ,","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"is this person a citizen of the United States ?","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"The Department of Justice earlier this week told us","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"that the printing has started","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"without this question for the 2020 census forms .","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"But then , the next day , President Trump tweeted","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"that he essentially has -","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"any reports","depth":13},{"id":35,"text":"that the Commerce Department has given up on asking for this question ,","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"that 's -","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"those are not true ,","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"And so -","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"and that is a tweet","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"that essentially spurred a flurry of court activity yesterday -","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"different court hearings that -","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"was revealed","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"a Justice Department official said","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"that they are still looking now for a reason","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"to ask for a citizenship question .","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"KING :","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"OK , so they had their chance before the Supreme Court ,","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"and the Supreme Court said ,","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"no , you may not ask this question .","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"What was the Supreme Court 's reasoning ?","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"WANG :","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"The Supreme Court said ,","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"for now , you 're not allowed to ask this question","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"because a majority of the court found","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"that the administration 's justification for the question ,","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"that it would help better enforce part of the Voting Rights Act ,","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"better protect the voting rights of racial minorities ,","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"that that reasoning ,","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"quote ,","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"`` seems to have been contrived . ''","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"And so the justice","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"- and so the Supreme Court , rather , said","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"that ,","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"you know ,","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"the Commerce Department , the Commerce secretary","depth":14},{"id":67,"text":"who oversees the Census Bureau ,","depth":14},{"id":68,"text":"does have the authority","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"to add this question .","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"But there needs to be a legitimate reason ,","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"and that was not a legitimate reason here .","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"KING :","depth":6},{"id":73,"text":"And is it clear what the Justice Department intends to do","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"to come up with a legitimate reason ?","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"WANG :","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"Well , the Justice Department has said in a letter to a federal judge in New York ,","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"who is also wondering what is happening here -","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"that they are instructed to try to look for another way","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"to ask for the citizenship question","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"and get it onto the 2020 census forms .","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"And that would require figuring out a new justification for this question .","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"And the big question then is ,","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"once the Trump administration announces","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"it has a new justification for this question ,","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"would it pass the test of the courts ?","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"Will the courts now believe","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"that that is a reasonable and also a legal way","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"to get this question on the census ?","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"KING :","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"OK .","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"So what happens next ?","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"There is n't a new deadline now , right ?","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"WANG :","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"The deadline now is Friday 2 p.m. Eastern .","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"A federal judge in Maryland - this is a very complicated legal battle .","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"A judge in Maryland says","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"the Justice Department has to inform his court what happens going forward .","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"Does the Trump administration intend to try to make another case for a citizenship question ,","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"because it really hinges then on ,","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"if there are plans to do that ,","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"a federal judge in Maryland is ready to reopen and reconsider already-filed allegations against this question ,","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"that the decision","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"to add this question","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"was intended to discriminate against immigrant communities of color","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"and that there was a conspiracy amongst Trump administration officials .","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"KING :","depth":5},{"id":108,"text":"And in the meantime , we should keep reminding people , like , the sand is running through the hourglass here , right ?","depth":5},{"id":109,"text":"It 's a 2020 census .","depth":4},{"id":110,"text":"WANG :","depth":5},{"id":111,"text":"It is coming .","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"It officially starts in January .","depth":7},{"id":113,"text":"Most people may not be thinking about it ,","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"but we are in the last stages of preparations .","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"And so getting the forms printed , finalizing what questions are on the form","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"is very important","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"to make sure","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"a count happens on time .","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"And this is a count of every person","depth":5},{"id":120,"text":"living in the country .","depth":5},{"id":121,"text":"KING :","depth":4},{"id":122,"text":"NPR 's Hansi Lo Wang","depth":7},{"id":123,"text":"covering the census ,","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"thinking about the census .","depth":6},{"id":125,"text":"Thanks , Hansi .","depth":5},{"id":126,"text":"NPR transcripts are created on a rush deadline by Verb8tm , Inc. , an NPR contractor ,","depth":6},{"id":127,"text":"and produced","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"using a proprietary transcription process","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"developed with NPR .","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"This text may not be in its final form","depth":7},{"id":131,"text":"and may be updated or revised in the future .","depth":7},{"id":132,"text":"Accuracy and availability may vary .","depth":6},{"id":133,"text":"The authoritative record of NPR ' s programming is the audio record .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":267,"left":240,"right":266,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":240,"left":150,"right":239,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":150,"left":0,"right":149,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":149,"left":143,"right":148,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":143,"left":140,"right":142,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":140,"left":136,"right":139,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":136,"left":1,"right":135,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":135,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":139,"left":4,"right":138,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":138,"left":5,"right":137,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":137,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":142,"left":8,"right":141,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":141,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":148,"left":145,"right":147,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":145,"left":11,"right":144,"relatio